A4.text: Caroline Bouvier Kennedy... is a member of the Kennedy family and the only surviving child of President John F. Kennedy and First Lady Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis.

A5.text: Caroline and John Jr.'s uncle Robert F. Kennedy became a major presence in both children's lives following their father's assassination, and Kennedy saw Robert as a surrogate father.

A6.text: Robert F. Kennedy had a brother named John F. Kennedy

A7.text: Joseph P. Kennedy Jr. was one of Robert F. Kennedy's siblings

A8.text: Jacqueline Kennedy gave birth to a stillborn daughter, Arabella, in August 1956.

A9.text: Joseph and Rose Kennedy were Jacqueline Kennedy's parents-in-law.
